                    "@type": "Answer",
                    text: "Yes. The G4AL uses a belt-driven SOHC interference design. If the timing belt fails, pistons will contact open valves, causing bent valves and potentially catastrophic engine damage. Strict adherence to the 60,000 km belt replacement interval is essential.",
