            heading: "Practical Implications",
            content: `The belt-driven SOHC and MPFI system provide excellent serviceability but result in modest power and higher fuel consumption compared to modern engines. Timing belt replacement every 60,000 km is critical to prevent valve damage in this interference design. Hydraulic lifter ticking is common in high-mileage units using incorrect oil viscosity or suffering from low oil pressure—use only API SG/SH 10W-30/40 oil. The engine lacks variable valve timing or advanced emissions controls, simplifying repairs but limiting compliance in low-emission zones. Ethanol blends above E5 may degrade fuel lines and seals.`,
