          subheading: `The G4DF's primary reliability risk is timing belt failure due to infrequent replacement, with elevated incidence in high-mileage urban vehicles. Hyundai internal service data (2004) indicated bent valves in over 18% of engines exceeding 80,000 km without belt service, while UK DVSA records show minimal emissions-related MOT failures due to the engine's basic Euro 2 compliance. Hydraulic lifter wear and oil gallery sludge further accelerate valve train degradation, making service discipline critical.`,
