            content: `The DOHC layout provides smooth and linear power delivery ideal for city and motorway use but requires consistent oil changes every 10,000 km to prevent camshaft lobe wear, especially in early units (pre-06/2017). Hyundai SP 5W‑30 oil (API SN/ILSAC GF‑5) is critical due to its additive package supporting valve train durability. The engine uses a maintenance-free timing chain, but oil degradation accelerates wear on cam followers under high load. Fuel must meet EN 228 standards; ethanol blends above E10 may degrade injector seals over time. Revised camshafts from mid-2017 onward resolve the lobe wear issue per TSB‑ENG‑112.`,
