            heading: "Practical Implications",
            content: `The D‑CVVT system enhances low-end torque and fuel economy but relies on clean oil circulation; infrequent oil changes can accelerate chain wear despite its “maintenance-free” designation. Hyundai SP 5W-30 (or ACEA A5/B5 equivalent) is essential to maintain hydraulic actuator performance and reduce sludge. The MPFI system avoids direct-injection carbon issues on pistons but still permits intake valve deposits under short-trip conditions. Post-2014 ECU updates improve cold-start enrichment to mitigate this. No timing belt replacement is required, but oil quality directly affects long-term chain and actuator reliability.`,
