            content: `The VGT turbo and high-pressure common-rail system deliver strong low-RPM torque ideal for towing and highway overtaking, but require strict adherence to 15,000 km oil change intervals using ACEA C2/C3 5W‑30 oil to protect the timing chain and fuel pump. The SCR/AdBlue system mandates regular fluid top-ups and periodic DPF regeneration cycles; ignoring warnings can trigger limp mode. Cold-start idling should be minimized to reduce wear on the high-pressure pump drive. Post-2018 models feature a reinforced pump coupling per Hyundai SIB EM‑17‑12, improving long-term reliability.`,
